cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO

This paper is about using genetic algorithms to train deep neural networks for reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on Atari games and humanoid locomotion, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the parallelization of the algorithm, which could suggest that it could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
